*Summary*
Unable to update username using JIRA REST API in Cloud

*Steps to reproduce*
- Send https://{instance_URL}/rest/api/2/user?username={username that you want to modify}
- JSON: { "name": "test" }
- It will produce the error like below:
{noformat}
{
    "errorMessages": [
        "This user can not be renamed because that operation is unsupported by the underlying user directory or JIRA is acting as a Crowd Server."
    ],
    "errors": {}
}
{noformat}

*Expected Behaviour*
Based on this documentation https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/ondemand/#d2e5367 , we should be able to modify the username in Cloud.

*Affects Versions*
- 6.5-OD-08-001

Most of Cloud users when they try to sign in using Google Apps, they get stuck on an URL similar to:{noformat}
https://redirect.useast.atlassian.io/google-callback.html#state=dest-url%3D%252Fsecure%252FMyJiraHome.jspa%26xsrf%3D584375-fsdkjhiu4yiuerhg%26host%3Dinstance.atlassian.net&access_token=kjshgkjsdhgjkhsdfkjglhsdlfkjghlkjsdfhglk&token_type=Bearer&expires_in=3600{noformat}

Which returns a 404 with the message {{Cannot GET /google-callback.html}}.

This issue is fixed now!

Its currently possible for Cloud Admins to change/update the description for all groups. This can cause confusion. 

For example, I found a case where a customer updated the description for the system-administrators group that states: 
{quote}
Wrapper around System Administrator role; likely deprecated
{quote}
As we know, the default group description states:
{quote}
Reserved for use by Atlassian Support to perform system maintenance tasks
{quote}
Ideally, we can lock down the description fields for Atlassian service accounts and groups.

h4. Symptom

When trying to connect to GApps new configuration, the following message is displayed:

{code}
"Error getting user list from Google:
{
  "code" : 403,
  "errors" : [
    { "domain" : "global", "message" : "Domain cannot use apis.", "reason" : "domainCannotUseApis" }
  ],
  "message" : "Domain cannot use apis."
}"
{code}

h4. Cause
Your Google Apps domain is configured to disallow API access. Without this access Atlassian Cloud is unable to access the APIs that it requires in order to read user information from your domain.

h4. Resolution
You need to [enable the administrative APIs|https://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=701596277] in the Google Apps Control Panel.
